
TOUCH COMMAND 
-----------------

Create file using touch command

>stat file1

touch command
    -to change the timestamp of the file 
    -creates 0 byte file(empty)

    >touch f1 f2 f3 f4
    >ll
    >touch K{1..5}
    > ls -l
        see the timestamp

to cahnge the timestamp of file::

syntax:: 
# touch -d "yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss" file name


ex:: #touch -d "2023-01-01 11:22:44" File1

#ls -l

why to cahnge then time stamp of file/directory
=>some files in servers cannot synchronize bcoz of 
different timesatmp so we need to match time to synchronize with server


some options available 

>touch -a  filename 
     - changes access time of the file named Doc1.

>touch -c filename 
    - check if file is created or not, if not then create


>stat file1

>touch -m filename
    - change only the modification time of a file.



